          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1585748046591-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and roughly chop your<strong> shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and roughly chop your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Peel and roughly chop your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>red</strong> <strong>chilli[es]</strong> roughly (not a fan of spice? Remove the seeds!)</p><p>Chop your<strong> lime leaf[ves] </strong>roughly</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1585748051440-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1585748051440-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1585748051440-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1585748051440-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1585748051440-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped shallot</strong>, <strong>ginger</strong>, <strong>garlic</strong>, <strong>chopped lime leaf[ves]</strong> and <strong>ground turmeric </strong>to a<strong> food processor</strong> with the <strong>chopped red chilli</strong> and<strong> chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp] </span><strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Blitz into a paste – this is your<strong> fiery sambal</strong></p><p>Tip: No food processor? Chop everything up as finely as you can and mix it together!</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1585748057562-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1585748057562-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1585748057562-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1585748057562-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1585748057562-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> fiery sambal</strong> and cook for 2 min or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1585748061645-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1585748061645-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1585748061645-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1585748061645-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1585748061645-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the fiery sambal<strong> </strong>is cooking, dissolve your <strong>tamarind paste</strong> in 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[450ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Add 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp]<strong> </span>sugar </strong>and your <strong>soy sauce</strong> and stir it all together – this is your <strong>tamarind stock</strong></p><p>Rinse your <strong>blanched edamame beans</strong> under <strong>cold running water</strong></p><p>Drain your<strong> king prawns</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1585748065673-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1585748065673-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1585748065673-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1585748065673-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1585748065673-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>tamarind stock</strong> to the pan with the fiery sambal and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat, then add the<strong> king prawns</strong> to the pan along with the <strong>blanched</strong> <strong>edamame beans</strong></p><p>Cook for 4-5 min or until the prawns are cooked through and the edamame beans are tender with a bite – this is your <strong>Indonesian-style</strong> <strong>fiery king prawn broth</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
